c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Amie is best suited for professionals, freelancers, calendar power users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Taskade, meanwhile, shines for remote teams, AI enthusiasts, small teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Amie describes itself as \"Joyful calendar app combining scheduling, tasks, and availability sharing.\" Taskade, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI-powered workspace with custom AI agents for tasks, notes, and projects.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Taskade** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Amie is a poor choice — far from it. Amie excels in its own right, particularly for professionals and freelancers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value custom ai agents for different workflows, go with Taskade. If beautiful and joyful design matters more to you, Amie is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
